2019年，[[Netflix|Netflix]]上架《新世纪福音战士》，其全新的英语版配音引发很大的争议。其中，渚薰在浴场对真嗣说的台词「{{lang|ja|好き}}」，原先的北美配音译为「I love you」（我爱你），新版却改成更为委婉的「I like you」（我喜欢你）。许多粉丝对此表示不满，指责Netflix意图淡化渚薰和真嗣间的同性恋色彩。负责翻译的兼光丹尼尔真（Dan Kanemitsu）回应说他做翻译时，都是尽可能地呈现原意，此次也不例外；他还表示留下诠释空间会更有趣<ref>{{cite web |author=Aja Romano |title=Netflix's re-translation of Neon Genesis Evangelion is drawing backlash for queer erasure |url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/6/24/18701179/netflix-neon-genesis-evangelion-kaworu-gay-backlash |website=Vox |language=en |date=2019-06-24 |access-date=2021-01-10 |archive-date=2019-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701102316/https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/6/24/18701179/netflix-neon-genesis-evangelion-kaworu-gay-backlash |dead-url=no }}</ref>。曾負責《福音戰士新劇場版》系列香港中文版翻译工作的Peggy也表达了自己的看法，她认为「like」更加贴近日语原意，并且更为合理<ref>{{cite web |author=鍾世傑 |title=NETFLIX《新世紀 EVA》又惹火 英文對白Love變Like疑沖淡BL味？ |url=https://www.hk01.com/%E9%81%8A%E6%88%B2%E5%8B%95%E6%BC%AB/345335/ |website=香港01 |date=2019-06-27 |access-date=2021-01-10 |archive-date=2021-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210726181531/https://www.hk01.com/%E9%81%8A%E6%88%B2%E5%8B%95%E6%BC%AB/345335/netflix-%E6%96%B0%E4%B8%96%E7%B4%80-eva-%E5%8F%88%E6%83%B9%E7%81%AB-%E8%8B%B1%E6%96%87%E5%B0%8D%E7%99%BDlove%E8%AE%8Alike%E7%96%91%E6%B2%96%E6%B7%A1bl%E5%91%B3 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但这种解释并未完全说服粉丝，動畫新聞網的金·莫里西（Kim Morrissy）觉得「love」更符合故事情境，这还涉及文化差异，因为日本人表达爱意时比较含蓄<ref>{{cite web |author=Kim Morrissy |title=Japanese Fans, Official Translator Weigh in on Netflix Evangelion English Subtitle Debate |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-06-27/japanese-fans-official-translator-weigh-in-on-netflix-evangelion-english-subtitle-debate/.148305 |website=Anime News Network |date=2019-06-28 |language=en |access-date=2021-01-10 |archive-date=2020-05-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530045243/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-06-27/japanese-fans-official-translator-weigh-in-on-netflix-evangelion-english-subtitle-debate/.148305 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

渚薰和真嗣是日本动画中最受欢迎的同性恋组合之一，他们的关系获得广泛关注和讨论，被高度评价为少数主流动画中涉及主角的相对积极的同性恋关系之一<ref>{{cite web |author=Tom Foster |title=The Top Five LGBT Couples in Anime |url=https://www.tvovermind.com/top-five-lgbt-couples-anime/ |website=TVOvermind |date=2018-08-04 |language=en |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2021-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210724191842/https://www.tvovermind.com/top-five-lgbt-couples-anime/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=reelrundown>{{cite web |author=Rachael Lefler |title=Why Kaworu and Shinji's Relationship Matters to the Story of Evangelion |url=https://reelrundown.com/animation/Why-Kaworu-and-Shinjis-Relationship-Matters-to-the-Story-of-Evangelion |website=ReelRundown |language=en |date=2020-08-21 |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2021-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116175952/https://reelrundown.com/animation/Why-Kaworu-and-Shinjis-Relationship-Matters-to-the-Story-of-Evangelion |dead-url=no }}</ref>。漫画书资源网（CBR.com）将薰和真嗣列为日本动画最佳[[酷儿|酷儿]]代表，认为他们的同性恋关系是超前于时代的<ref>{{cite web |author=Caleb Bailey |title=Neon Genesis Evangelion: 5 Ways The Anime Was Ahead Of Its Time (& 5 Ways It Wasn't) |url=https://www.cbr.com/neon-genesis-evangelion-anime-ahead-of-time-criticism/ |website=CBR |language=en |date=2019-11-18 |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2020-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329142741/https://www.cbr.com/neon-genesis-evangelion-anime-ahead-of-time-criticism/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Anthony Gramuglia |title=The Best (and Worst) Anime Starring Queer Guys |url=https://www.cbr.com/best-worst-anime-queer-guys-evangelion-yuri-gravitation/ |website=CBR |language=en |date=2020-06-06 |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127131234/https://www.cbr.com/best-worst-anime-queer-guys-evangelion-yuri-gravitation/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。面向[[LGBT|LGBT]]的门户网站Pride.com也称赞了他们的关系，肯定他们带来的巨大影响，尤其是在那个LGBTQ几乎不见于多媒体的时代<ref>{{cite web |author=Cassie Sheets |title=8 LGBTQ+ Anime Worth Binging—And Where to Watch Them |url=https://www.pride.com/geek/2020/9/29/8-lgbtq-anime-worth-binging-and-where-watch-them |website=PRIDE |language=en |date=2020-09-29 |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2021-02-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213234758/https://www.pride.com/geek/2020/9/29/8-lgbtq-anime-worth-binging-and-where-watch-them |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Raffy Ermac |title=Queer Fans Aren't Happy With Netflix's 'Neon Genesis Evangelion' Dub |url=https://www.pride.com/geek/2019/6/26/queer-fans-arent-happy-netflixs-neon-genesis-evangelion-dub |website=PRIDE |language=en |date=2019-06-26 |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2020-07-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730172600/https://www.pride.com/geek/2019/6/26/queer-fans-arent-happy-netflixs-neon-genesis-evangelion-dub |dead-url=no }}</ref>。也有评论指出，同性恋问题无非是吸引该类型粉丝的策略<ref>{{cite web |author=Kenneth Lee |title=The Thin Veneer Known as "Evangelion" |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/editorial/1998-09-09 |website=Anime News Network |date=1998-09-09 |language=en |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2017-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724103237/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/editorial/1998-09-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>；不过，在一部主流动画中任何同性恋描写都是一种进步<ref name=reelrundown />。

=== 评论 ===
{{quote|真嗣没怎么被他人肯定过。只有薰对他说「你现在这样就很好」「不那么努力也没关系」。因此有趣的是，本以为女性观众们不会变得和男孩子一样狂热，但从薰出场以来，她们才第一次对真嗣这个角色有了情感代入。或许大家都很喜欢薰呢。|几原邦彦<ref name=Kaworu />{{rp|54-55}}}}

日本作家谷崎Tetra把薰看作是「守护天使」般的存在，薰在真嗣最为脆弱的时候出现，对真嗣给予肯定。谷崎认为，对于被孤独感和对他人的恐惧感侵袭的多数现代人来说，这小小的肯定是极为重要的，是活下去的希望<ref name=Kaworu />{{rp|60}}。评论家亚伦·普洛夫（Aaron Ploof）认为薰是一个[[耶稣基督|耶稣基督]]般的角色，不惜放弃自己的生命，以便人类能够掌握自己的未来<ref>{{cite web |author1=Aaron Ploof |title=Neon Genesis Evangelion: Rei and Kaworu |url=https://25yearslatersite.com/2019/06/20/neon-genesis-evangelion-rei-and-kaworu/ |website=25YL |date=2019-06-20 |language=en |access-date=2021-07-24 |archive-date=2020-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815143326/https://25yearslatersite.com/2019/06/20/neon-genesis-evangelion-rei-and-kaworu/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。据评论家野火Nobita分析，真嗣只在渚薰面前才想舍弃伪我而表现出真正的自我，因为渚薰是一个能接受真嗣的整个存在的完美的人，他不仅道出了被真嗣隐蔽的自我，还对真嗣表现出过剩的好意<ref>{{cite book |author=野火ノビタ |chapter=大人は判ってくれない |editor=五十嵐太郎 |script-title=ja:『エヴァンゲリオン快楽原則』 |publisher=第三書館 |isbn=978-4807497263 |year=1997 |language=ja}}</ref>。

日本精神科医生、评论家名越康文分析称，薰是一个贯彻了“阴性感情类型”本质的角色，即总是面带微笑、散发着温柔气场、对他人持有丰厚同情心的“治愈系”男子。这种类型的人对他人的感觉和感情有异常高的感应力，对自己情绪的感应力却很低。名越认为，薰对他人的高感应力源自他自身的虚无，从虚无再而萌生出对真嗣强烈的支配欲望，最终他的愿望即为：通过自身的死亡，在对方心中最深处，刻下关于自己的记忆。至于薰的人气如此之高，名越认为理由有二。其一、他的自我牺牲，是一个带有宗教神话性质的构造，成为粉丝们追捧的对象。其次、薰是一个高度提纯了的动画角色，特色分明；角色几乎没有背景故事，高度记号化。<ref name=Kaworu />{{rp|56-57}}

